    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="197"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/938</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Far Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hamilton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-15">October 15,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Welles</hi>: Mr. Hornbeck and I, upon giving further
                    consideration to the matter, are of the opinion that if Mr. Browder is to give
                    out and publish the other statement which you gave him<note n="54"
                        xml:id="d197fn54">See statement of October 12, <ref target="#pg_248">p.
                            248</ref>.</note> it would be well for Mr. Browder to publish this
                        statement<note n="55" xml:id="d197fn55">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> also.</p>
                <p>(If this statement is to be sent to him, the first page would need to be retyped
                    in as much as it bears the FE date stamp.)<note n="56" xml:id="d197fn56">In
                        reply to an inquiry dated May 19, 1950, Mr. Hamilton wrote on May 26: “I
                        have no recollection of having had any knowledge regarding the occasion of
                        Mr. Browder’s call or of the statement handed to Mr. Browder by Mr. Welles
                        until after Mr. Browder had called and had been given the statement”
                        (893.01/938).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M[<hi rend="smallcaps">axwell</hi>] M. H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >amilton</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
